1
00:00:10,567 --> 00:00:13,067
<i>Clean up the entire gym,
even the bleachers.</i>

2
00:00:14,567 --> 00:00:15,767
<i>These are the guys trending
right now!</i>

3
00:00:15,900 --> 00:00:17,267
<i>This is the first time
I saw your faces.</i>

4
00:00:17,400 --> 00:00:19,000
<i>Easy, just chill.
We don't want trouble.</i>

5
00:00:19,133 --> 00:00:21,367
<i>We want you to try out
for the taekwondo team.</i>

6
00:00:21,500 --> 00:00:23,800
<i>Are you challenging us just
to join the taekwondo team?</i>

7
00:00:23,933 --> 00:00:25,333
<i> You guys are crazy!</i>

8
00:00:25,467 --> 00:00:26,600
<i>Come on, these guys are cowards.</i>

9
00:00:26,733 --> 00:00:28,067
<i>It's a good thing
you stayed away from Jako.</i>

10
00:00:28,200 --> 00:00:30,867
<i>His brother was in jail
for using illegal substances,</i>

11
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:33,433
<i>the current trend,
the pimple patch drugs.</i>

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:35,200
<i> Is Monty Espina his brother?</i>

13
00:00:35,333 --> 00:00:36,300
<i> Do you know him?</i>

14
00:00:36,433 --> 00:00:38,767
<i>Sir, have you heard?
Bobby met his father!</i>

15
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:41,200
<i>None other than Mayor Guerrero!</i>

16
00:00:41,333 --> 00:00:43,267
<i>Bobby's father
is Mayor Guerrero?</i>

17
00:00:43,400 --> 00:00:44,933
<i>Both of you are children
of action stars.</i>

18
00:00:45,067 --> 00:00:46,900
<i>That's not all. They are also
rivals in politics.</i>

19
00:00:47,033 --> 00:00:47,967
<i> Hi, Bobby.</i>

20
00:00:48,100 --> 00:00:50,033
<i> Bobby, what brings you here?</i>

21
00:00:50,167 --> 00:00:51,700
<i> I invited them for lunch.</i>

22
00:00:51,833 --> 00:00:52,967
<i> Nice to see you again.</i>

23
00:00:53,100 --> 00:00:55,433
<i>I never thought I'd have
a sibling who is a Sergeant.</i>

24
00:00:55,567 --> 00:00:56,900
<i> Excuse me, Sir.</i>

25
00:00:57,033 --> 00:00:58,100
<i> Master Sergeant.</i>

26
00:00:58,233 --> 00:00:59,533
<i> Congratulations, Bobby.</i>

27
00:00:59,667 --> 00:01:01,600
<i>You didn't say your daughter
was invited.</i>

28
00:01:01,733 --> 00:01:03,867
<i>I would've worn something nicer.</i>

29
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:05,733
<i> Oh, no, you don't need to.</i>

30
00:01:05,867 --> 00:01:08,467
<i>Whatever you wear,
you still look beautiful.</i>

31
00:01:08,633 --> 00:01:09,667
<i> Is that Bobby?</i>

32
00:01:09,800 --> 00:01:11,433
<i>You already know what to do,
Cheka.</i>

33
00:01:11,567 --> 00:01:12,167
<i> Bobby?</i>

34
00:01:12,300 --> 00:01:13,567
<i> What's Bobby doing here?</i>

35
00:01:15,867 --> 00:01:18,900
Bobby, try all the food.
Everything's delicious.

36
00:01:19,033 --> 00:01:20,600
Okay, later.

37
00:01:20,733 --> 00:01:21,333
That's true.

38
00:01:21,467 --> 00:01:23,000
- Captain...
- Thank you.

39
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:23,933
Let's eat.

40
00:01:24,067 --> 00:01:25,200
There's a lot of food.

41
00:01:25,333 --> 00:01:29,700
Oh my, Vice, I'm still full,
and I have high blood pressure.

42
00:01:29,833 --> 00:01:30,700
Is that so?

43
00:01:30,833 --> 00:01:32,267
Me too, I also have maintenance
medications.

44
00:01:32,400 --> 00:01:36,200
Vice Mayor, why don't you
just offer it to us?

45
00:01:36,333 --> 00:01:39,033
Oh, yes, whatever it is,
we'll swallow it.

46
00:01:39,167 --> 00:01:40,233
Yes.

47
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,667
Nothing goes to waste.

48
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:47,967
Bobby, tell us...

49
00:01:48,100 --> 00:01:49,867
how many people have you killed?

50
00:01:50,700 --> 00:01:52,700
- Sophia, what a question...
- Mom...

51
00:01:52,833 --> 00:01:53,967
You shouldn't be talking
about that.

52
00:01:54,100 --> 00:01:56,367
What? Oh, okay, I'll change it.

53
00:01:56,500 --> 00:01:57,833
Let's talk about something else.

54
00:01:58,933 --> 00:02:00,333
Do you have a boyfriend?

55
00:02:01,433 --> 00:02:02,967
I don't.

56
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:07,533
Well, just make sure that
if you get a boyfriend,

57
00:02:07,667 --> 00:02:09,533
get someone single.

58
00:02:09,667 --> 00:02:11,700
So you don't end up
like your mother.

59
00:02:11,833 --> 00:02:13,767
Sophia, what kind of question
is that again?

60
00:02:13,900 --> 00:02:16,033
It's true.

61
00:02:16,200 --> 00:02:18,500
I haven't killed anyone yet,

62
00:02:18,633 --> 00:02:19,767
but maybe I will now.

63
00:02:58,500 --> 00:03:00,133
Excuse me, Captain.

64
00:03:00,267 --> 00:03:01,300
Is that a threat?

65
00:03:01,433 --> 00:03:02,833
Yes.

66
00:03:02,967 --> 00:03:05,767
Try saying something
against my daughter,

67
00:03:05,900 --> 00:03:07,367
and I'll do what I said earlier.

68
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:08,433
Sophia...

69
00:03:09,567 --> 00:03:10,300
come on.

70
00:03:10,433 --> 00:03:13,033
Captain, I'm sorry.

71
00:03:16,033 --> 00:03:16,600
Hello?

72
00:03:17,833 --> 00:03:18,900
You're here already?

73
00:03:19,033 --> 00:03:21,167
Okay, I'll fetch you.

74
00:03:21,333 --> 00:03:24,700
Mom, Dad, I invited
my girlfriend,

75
00:03:24,833 --> 00:03:26,700
so you can meet her too.

76
00:03:26,833 --> 00:03:27,800
Oh, okay.

77
00:03:27,933 --> 00:03:29,300
- Okay, I'll just get her.
- Okay, let her in.

78
00:03:38,133 --> 00:03:40,000
That's really brave
of Captain Isang.

79
00:03:40,133 --> 00:03:41,633
You think Captain Isang
can take it?

80
00:03:41,767 --> 00:03:43,800
The mayor's wife has tons
of bodyguards.

81
00:03:43,933 --> 00:03:45,567
She thought we were going
to help her.

82
00:03:45,700 --> 00:03:47,900
Oh, no, they have a lot of guns.
I don't want to die.

83
00:03:48,033 --> 00:03:49,700
We'll side with the mayor's
wife, okay?

84
00:03:49,833 --> 00:03:53,467
Yes, of course,
let's prioritize our beauty.

85
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,667
- Go on, finish your food.
- I don't want to die early.

86
00:03:55,833 --> 00:03:57,633
Mom, Dad...

87
00:03:57,767 --> 00:04:00,400
my girlfriend,
Doc Cecilia Montero.

88
00:04:02,733 --> 00:04:03,933
Bobby?

89
00:04:04,067 --> 00:04:05,033
Doc Cecilia...

90
00:04:06,400 --> 00:04:08,500
Are you the vice mayor's
girlfriend?

91
00:04:10,067 --> 00:04:11,033
Yeah, yeah.

92
00:04:12,300 --> 00:04:14,233
I didn't know you two
knew each other.

93
00:04:14,367 --> 00:04:18,067
Anyway, Bobby is my half-sister.

94
00:04:18,200 --> 00:04:19,233
What?

95
00:04:19,367 --> 00:04:20,300
Yeah.

96
00:04:43,600 --> 00:04:44,500
Hey, Mando!

97
00:04:50,267 --> 00:04:51,367
Your radish looks good.

98
00:04:51,500 --> 00:04:53,167
Thank you, Sir.

99
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,833
We'll cook Sinigang later.

100
00:04:54,967 --> 00:04:56,133
By the way...

101
00:04:56,267 --> 00:04:59,200
Mando, this is Asuncion.

102
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:00,633
He'll be assigned here.

103
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:02,300
Good afternoon, Sir.

104
00:05:02,433 --> 00:05:04,433
Mando's a good guy.

105
00:05:04,567 --> 00:05:06,033
He's got a good record here.

106
00:05:06,167 --> 00:05:08,333
That's why he's among those who
will be transferred to Batangas.

107
00:05:08,467 --> 00:05:09,633
Thank you, Sir.

108
00:05:09,767 --> 00:05:11,833
We'll go ahead, Mando.
We'll just do our rounds.

109
00:05:11,967 --> 00:05:13,233
Okay, Sir. Be careful!

110
00:05:14,900 --> 00:05:16,000
Sir...

111
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:16,967
Is he...

112
00:05:17,100 --> 00:05:17,933
Mandong Warak?

113
00:05:18,067 --> 00:05:19,200
The guy who's angry
with the police?

114
00:05:19,333 --> 00:05:20,333
That was before.

115
00:05:20,467 --> 00:05:22,267
Did he get his wound here?

116
00:05:22,400 --> 00:05:26,267
No, it was because of Conde,
my classmate back then.

117
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:28,600
Let's go.

118
00:05:28,733 --> 00:05:29,200
Let's go.

119
00:05:32,433 --> 00:05:32,967
Romel...

120
00:05:36,000 --> 00:05:38,567
we're finally moving
to Batangas.

121
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:40,967
What are we going to do
with Sir Mike?

122
00:05:41,933 --> 00:05:43,133
Sir Mike asked to add some more.

123
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:44,500
One hundred.

124
00:05:44,633 --> 00:05:46,033
What will we do?

125
00:05:46,167 --> 00:05:48,500
Find me a cell phone.

126
00:05:48,633 --> 00:05:51,533
I'll call my old boss.

127
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:54,367
We're almost out of prison.

128
00:05:54,500 --> 00:05:57,033
We've been planning this
for so long.

129
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:01,333
It's happening very soon.

130
00:06:02,433 --> 00:06:04,233
I'm going back to our province,
Mando.

131
00:06:04,367 --> 00:06:05,900
You can come with me.

132
00:06:06,033 --> 00:06:09,300
No, I'll just stay here
in Calabari.

133
00:06:09,467 --> 00:06:11,467
The police should be ready
for me.

134
00:06:11,600 --> 00:06:16,100
I'll take them all down one by
one until I reach Antonio Conde.

135
00:06:16,233 --> 00:06:20,633
I'll skin him alive
before I chop up his body.

136
00:06:20,767 --> 00:06:23,333
Just a little bit more.
Get ready for me.

137
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,433
<i> Stop that!</i>

138
00:06:31,100 --> 00:06:32,267
<i> Mando Garrido!</i>

139
00:06:33,933 --> 00:06:34,933
<i> Let go of that.</i>

140
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,200
<i> Hands up!</i>

141
00:06:38,333 --> 00:06:39,633
<i> You look like a rookie.</i>

142
00:06:41,000 --> 00:06:42,400
<i>I've never killed
a rookie before.</i>

143
00:07:08,733 --> 00:07:10,100
What a small world.

144
00:07:10,233 --> 00:07:11,567
Come on, sit down, come on.

145
00:07:11,700 --> 00:07:12,633
- Thank you.
- Let's eat.

146
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:15,533
Let's eat.

147
00:07:15,667 --> 00:07:17,567
Please give Cecilia some food.

148
00:07:17,700 --> 00:07:19,000
Maybe you're hungry.

149
00:07:22,133 --> 00:07:23,133
Faye...

150
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:25,900
please...

151
00:07:26,033 --> 00:07:29,100
don't bring a boyfriend
with you, okay?

152
00:07:29,233 --> 00:07:30,867
Let your sister go first.

153
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,200
Daddy, I don't have a boyfriend!

154
00:07:33,333 --> 00:07:36,433
With that pretty face,
you don't have a boyfriend?

155
00:07:36,567 --> 00:07:38,467
Excuse me, it's hot.

156
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:43,100
- Sorry. Oh my, I'm sorry.
- Oh my God, Cheka!

157
00:07:43,233 --> 00:07:45,500
- You're so stupid!
- Oh my, I'm sorry!

158
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:46,533
- I'm sorry!
- You're so clumsy!

159
00:07:46,667 --> 00:07:47,833
Aren't you ashamed
in front of our guest?

160
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,733
I'm really sorry. I'm sorry!

161
00:07:49,867 --> 00:07:50,700
You're so stupid!

162
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:52,800
I didn't mean to.
I'm really sorry, Mayor.

163
00:07:52,933 --> 00:07:54,067
What are you doing?

164
00:07:54,200 --> 00:07:55,067
I'm sorry.

165
00:07:55,200 --> 00:07:56,000
You're not looking
at what you're doing.

166
00:07:56,133 --> 00:07:58,300
- No, I'm fine.
- No. It's not okay.

167
00:07:58,433 --> 00:08:00,000
Let's go to the comfort room.
Let's clean that.

168
00:08:00,133 --> 00:08:01,633
Let's just change it, okay?

169
00:08:01,767 --> 00:08:02,733
Excuse us.

170
00:08:02,867 --> 00:08:03,800
- It's really okay.
- I'm sorry. Ma'am, sorry.

171
00:08:03,933 --> 00:08:04,433
That's enough, Cheka.

172
00:08:04,600 --> 00:08:05,533
Go ahead.

173
00:08:05,667 --> 00:08:07,967
Come on, let's eat.

174
00:08:08,100 --> 00:08:09,667
Cecilia, let's eat. Come on.

175
00:08:15,167 --> 00:08:16,733
Sir Conde.

176
00:08:16,867 --> 00:08:19,633
Sir Gomez said he was sorry.

177
00:08:19,767 --> 00:08:21,267
He just left for a moment.

178
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,033
Is that so?

179
00:08:24,167 --> 00:08:26,033
No worries, we just brought
someone here.

180
00:08:26,167 --> 00:08:27,633
Send him my regards.

181
00:08:27,767 --> 00:08:29,167
I'll tell him that, Sir.

182
00:08:32,033 --> 00:08:35,633
Asuncion, is Mandong Warak here?

183
00:08:35,767 --> 00:08:38,833
I'm intrigued by the face
of the one Conde imprisoned.

184
00:08:38,967 --> 00:08:40,300
Where is he?

185
00:08:40,433 --> 00:08:41,700
Mando, Sir?

186
00:08:43,900 --> 00:08:44,833
There he is, Sir.

187
00:08:49,333 --> 00:08:51,300
Why is loitering here?

188
00:08:51,433 --> 00:08:54,067
Shouldn't he be in the maximum
prison area?

189
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:58,900
Sir Gomez said that
he's already a good guy.

190
00:08:59,033 --> 00:09:00,867
He has a good record here.

191
00:09:01,000 --> 00:09:04,033
We're not sure
if he's really changed.

192
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:06,467
He killed a lot of policemen.

193
00:09:06,600 --> 00:09:08,067
He's changed, Sir.

194
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,167
Let me call him.

195
00:09:10,167 --> 00:09:11,133
Mando!

196
00:09:16,267 --> 00:09:16,967
Sir Conde?

197
00:09:18,500 --> 00:09:19,800
Sir Conde...

198
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:21,100
Hey, Sir Conde!

199
00:09:23,867 --> 00:09:25,300
Sir Conde, how are you?

200
00:09:26,600 --> 00:09:27,433
I'm good.

201
00:09:28,967 --> 00:09:31,833
I heard you've changed.

202
00:09:31,967 --> 00:09:33,100
Yes, Sir.

203
00:09:33,233 --> 00:09:35,100
I've changed.

204
00:09:35,233 --> 00:09:37,400
I hope you'll forgive me.

205
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:51,300
You're cheating on me!

206
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:12,433
You can do it!

207
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:17,967
There's a police!

208
00:10:25,867 --> 00:10:28,633
Bok, it looks like Mando
really has changed.

209
00:10:28,767 --> 00:10:30,033
He saved your life.

210
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:33,000
Sir, thank you.

211
00:10:35,767 --> 00:10:39,700
Bobby, I'm really sorry
about Cheka.

212
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:41,867
Sometimes, she's really clumsy.

213
00:10:43,900 --> 00:10:46,667
You know what, I'll just have
that washed.

214
00:10:46,800 --> 00:10:49,467
There's a boutique here.
I'll just buy you some clothes.

215
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:50,733
No need.

216
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:53,467
Don't bother.

217
00:10:55,733 --> 00:10:58,533
I just want to be honest
with you, Ma'am Sophia.

218
00:10:58,667 --> 00:11:00,233
What do you mean?

219
00:11:00,367 --> 00:11:01,900
What is it, Bobby?

220
00:11:02,033 --> 00:11:05,033
I think you're the one who
ordered Cheka to do that to me.

221
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,267
Am I wrong?

222
00:11:12,367 --> 00:11:13,633
What do you mean?

223
00:11:14,900 --> 00:11:16,667
I'm asking you.

224
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:19,467
Did you order Cheka
to do that to me?

225
00:11:25,733 --> 00:11:28,167
What if it was me?

226
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:31,300
I wish you had just told me,
so I could have just left.

227
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:33,233
So it wouldn't even get
to the point

228
00:11:33,367 --> 00:11:34,867
where my uniform
would get dirty.

229
00:11:35,000 --> 00:11:37,500
I can accept it
if you don't like me.

230
00:11:37,633 --> 00:11:38,733
Excuse me.

231
00:11:40,233 --> 00:11:43,067
And why would I do that?

232
00:11:44,467 --> 00:11:47,033
I'll look like
an evil stepmother

233
00:11:47,167 --> 00:11:49,300
in front of my family,

234
00:11:49,433 --> 00:11:52,233
and you'll look like the victim.

235
00:11:52,367 --> 00:11:53,800
Well, with what you did,

236
00:11:53,933 --> 00:11:56,700
you proved that you really
are an evil stepmother.

237
00:11:58,367 --> 00:11:59,667
Don't worry.

238
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:02,167
This doesn't have to reach them.

239
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,400
If that's so,

240
00:12:03,533 --> 00:12:05,700
I wish you hadn't introduced
yourself as his daughter.

241
00:12:05,833 --> 00:12:07,200
You should have known

242
00:12:07,333 --> 00:12:10,000
that you would ruin my family
by doing that.

243
00:12:11,300 --> 00:12:15,767
But here you are,
feeling close with my daughter,

244
00:12:15,933 --> 00:12:19,533
eating at the same table
with my family

245
00:12:19,667 --> 00:12:23,633
that was almost ruined
because of your existence.

246
00:12:25,733 --> 00:12:28,700
You and your mother
are just the same...

247
00:12:28,833 --> 00:12:29,967
homewrecker.

248
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:34,767
Bobby is the mayor's
illegitimate daughter?

249
00:12:34,900 --> 00:12:36,800
Don't insult my mother.

250
00:12:36,933 --> 00:12:40,233
Your mother insulted me first!

251
00:12:40,367 --> 00:12:42,733
Go ahead, defend her.

252
00:12:42,867 --> 00:12:45,333
She had an affair
with a married man.

253
00:12:45,467 --> 00:12:47,500
Can't I sue her for something
like that?

254
00:12:47,633 --> 00:12:50,267
Okay, defend her.

255
00:12:54,400 --> 00:12:58,133
See? You can't even defend her.

256
00:12:58,267 --> 00:13:03,067
So don't force yourself
into my family.

257
00:13:04,767 --> 00:13:05,833
Copy.

258
00:13:23,367 --> 00:13:25,133
Who exactly is your old boss?

259
00:13:25,267 --> 00:13:27,033
Can he really help us?

260
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:30,133
He has a lot of money.

261
00:13:30,267 --> 00:13:32,100
He has a position in Calabari.

262
00:13:34,533 --> 00:13:36,033
A politician?

263
00:13:46,167 --> 00:13:50,333
Abdul, Mar,
where's Captain Isang?

264
00:13:50,467 --> 00:13:53,167
Vice, she's getting some air
by the pool.

265
00:13:53,300 --> 00:13:55,400
It seems like she doesn't
feel well.

266
00:13:55,567 --> 00:13:56,833
Is that so?

267
00:13:56,967 --> 00:14:02,167
I would like to apologize to her
for what my mother said and did.

268
00:14:02,300 --> 00:14:03,300
And to you, too.

269
00:14:05,367 --> 00:14:07,467
But I think Ma'am Sophia
realized

270
00:14:07,600 --> 00:14:09,267
that what she said was wrong.

271
00:14:09,400 --> 00:14:12,100
So she went with Bobby
to change her clothes, right?

272
00:14:12,233 --> 00:14:15,933
And I think she's apologizing
privately?

273
00:14:16,067 --> 00:14:16,967
Yeah.

274
00:14:18,567 --> 00:14:21,433
Well, let's eat some dessert
first.

275
00:14:21,567 --> 00:14:22,567
Let's try the dessert?

276
00:14:22,700 --> 00:14:24,667
If you need anything,
I'll be here.

277
00:14:24,800 --> 00:14:26,100
Okay.

278
00:14:36,267 --> 00:14:37,333
Hi.

279
00:14:37,467 --> 00:14:39,200
I'm Charlie.

280
00:14:39,333 --> 00:14:40,800
I heard everything.

281
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:45,900
You scolded Bobby thoroughly,
from head to soul.

282
00:14:46,033 --> 00:14:48,433
So she's the mayor's
illegitimate daughter,

283
00:14:48,567 --> 00:14:50,800
and you're her evil stepmother?

284
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,733
Is Bobby your friend?

285
00:14:53,867 --> 00:14:55,033
No.

286
00:14:55,167 --> 00:14:57,233
Colleagues but we're not close.

287
00:14:58,433 --> 00:15:01,700
I don't care even if
you're her best friend.

288
00:15:01,867 --> 00:15:03,567
She's still
an illegitimate child.

289
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:06,467
So don't you dare tell Joaquin
anything about it, okay?

290
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,033
Ma'am, calm down.

291
00:15:09,267 --> 00:15:11,300
Don't get me wrong.

292
00:15:11,433 --> 00:15:13,700
We both don't like Bobby.

293
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:16,200
But your reason seems deeper.

294
00:15:17,500 --> 00:15:18,867
So you hate her?

295
00:15:19,900 --> 00:15:21,500
Yes.

296
00:15:21,633 --> 00:15:25,600
Everyone who hates Bobby
is my friend.

297
00:15:28,500 --> 00:15:31,033
That's a good start
for a friendship.

298
00:15:33,100 --> 00:15:35,100
I'm Sophia Guerrero.

299
00:15:36,867 --> 00:15:38,467
Of course, I know you, Madam.

300
00:15:39,967 --> 00:15:41,767
Evil stepmother.

301
00:15:51,967 --> 00:15:53,200
It looks delicious.

302
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:55,600
Mar, Abdul.

303
00:15:56,633 --> 00:15:57,167
Hey, Bobby.

304
00:15:57,300 --> 00:15:58,867
Where's grandmother?

305
00:15:59,000 --> 00:16:00,167
I think she's getting some
fresh air by the pool.

306
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:01,867
She doesn't seem to be
feeling well.

307
00:16:02,000 --> 00:16:04,200
Yes, and her blood pressure
went up

308
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:06,400
because of what happened
earlier.

309
00:16:08,200 --> 00:16:10,567
Come on, let's go see
grandmother.

310
00:16:10,700 --> 00:16:11,367
Let's go home.

311
00:16:11,500 --> 00:16:12,267
What about the...

312
00:16:12,400 --> 00:16:12,867
We don't want to waste
the dessert.

313
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:14,933
That's enough, let's go.

314
00:16:15,067 --> 00:16:17,167
Even just a bite?

315
00:16:20,367 --> 00:16:21,233
Glen...

316
00:16:22,333 --> 00:16:23,833
where are the guests?

317
00:16:23,967 --> 00:16:25,533
Bobby and the others
left already.

318
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:33,133
Hey!

319
00:16:33,267 --> 00:16:34,600
Where's everyone?

320
00:16:34,733 --> 00:16:36,400
What did you do to my daughter?

321
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:40,967
I just told her off

322
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:45,233
because she came here with
people we don't even know,

323
00:16:45,400 --> 00:16:47,100
and now she's the one
who gets angry?

324
00:16:47,233 --> 00:16:49,833
Sophia, I invited them!

325
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:53,033
They're my guests.
What did you do?

326
00:16:53,167 --> 00:16:56,233
I just want to get to know
my daughter better,

327
00:16:56,367 --> 00:16:58,167
and the people around her.

328
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,233
Is that bad?

329
00:17:00,900 --> 00:17:03,200
Then you should have invited
the entire village

330
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:04,433
and the police station.

331
00:17:06,233 --> 00:17:07,000
Mom...

332
00:17:08,333 --> 00:17:11,233
Mom, you know that's not
what dad meant.

333
00:17:11,367 --> 00:17:13,700
Shut up, Glen.

334
00:17:13,833 --> 00:17:15,333
All of you,

335
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:19,633
you're always thinking of Bobby
as if she's the victim!

336
00:17:19,767 --> 00:17:25,300
Why hasn't anyone asked me
how I feel about everything?

337
00:17:25,433 --> 00:17:27,333
Mom, we talked about this
yesterday.

338
00:17:27,467 --> 00:17:29,233
Dad mentioned it yesterday.

339
00:17:29,367 --> 00:17:31,433
And I even asked you.

340
00:17:31,567 --> 00:17:32,733
You said you were okay with it.

341
00:17:32,867 --> 00:17:36,200
Of course I will say
that it's okay

342
00:17:36,333 --> 00:17:40,767
because I wanted to set a good
example for Faye.

343
00:17:40,900 --> 00:17:43,500
But ask any wife...

344
00:17:43,633 --> 00:17:45,500
if it's okay with her

345
00:17:45,633 --> 00:17:48,567
that her husband has a child
with his mistress...

346
00:17:50,333 --> 00:17:51,767
then you'll know the answer.

347
00:17:54,500 --> 00:17:55,467
Sophia...

348
00:17:56,933 --> 00:17:58,033
I'm sorry...

349
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:02,100
but Bobby is not at fault!

350
00:18:02,233 --> 00:18:05,667
It's not Bobby's fault
that she was born!

351
00:18:05,800 --> 00:18:08,700
I wish you had talked to me.

352
00:18:08,833 --> 00:18:11,433
I would have understood you.

353
00:18:11,567 --> 00:18:14,433
You want to know the truth,
Joaquin?

354
00:18:15,767 --> 00:18:20,533
I don't want that girl
near my family!

355
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:38,633
Let's get out of here,
Grandmother.

356
00:18:38,767 --> 00:18:39,833
Oh, yes.

357
00:18:39,967 --> 00:18:43,300
We're not welcome here.
Ma'am Sophia doesn't like me.

358
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:45,433
What?

359
00:18:45,567 --> 00:18:47,533
She's so fake!

360
00:18:47,667 --> 00:18:49,167
She was being nice earlier,

361
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:51,067
but it turns out she has
a really bad attitude!

362
00:18:51,200 --> 00:18:52,600
What did she do to you, Bobby?

363
00:18:52,733 --> 00:18:54,667
Did they oppress you? Hurt you?

364
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:55,900
Tell me!

365
00:18:56,067 --> 00:18:58,200
We'll perm her hair,
and her assistant's too.

366
00:18:58,333 --> 00:18:58,967
True.

367
00:18:59,100 --> 00:19:01,033
I'll talk to that Sophia!

368
00:19:01,167 --> 00:19:03,033
Grandmother, that's enough.

369
00:19:03,167 --> 00:19:05,067
Let's not make a big deal
out of this.

370
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,600
Ma'am Sophia has the right
to be angry.

371
00:19:08,900 --> 00:19:10,433
No matter what we do,

372
00:19:10,567 --> 00:19:13,733
I'm still seen as the child
of the mayor's mistress.

373
00:19:15,733 --> 00:19:17,400
That's why I understand her.

374
00:19:17,533 --> 00:19:18,667
Maybe when she saw me,

375
00:19:18,800 --> 00:19:22,100
she remembered the memories
she really wanted to forget

376
00:19:22,233 --> 00:19:22,967
all along.

377
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,167
Don't worry about it.

378
00:19:28,500 --> 00:19:29,933
Come on, let's go.

379
00:19:31,133 --> 00:19:32,367
- Bobby!
- I'm so annoyed!

380
00:19:32,500 --> 00:19:33,300
Me too.

381
00:19:36,400 --> 00:19:41,033
Bobby, I'm really sorry
for what my mom did earlier.

382
00:19:42,467 --> 00:19:44,000
Please don't leave yet.

383
00:19:45,233 --> 00:19:46,567
This clubhouse is big.

384
00:19:46,700 --> 00:19:49,000
We can go swimming
with my friends later.

385
00:19:49,133 --> 00:19:52,300
So please, Bobby, don't leave.

386
00:19:55,500 --> 00:19:59,700
Grandmother, go ahead.
I'll just go with Faye.

387
00:19:59,833 --> 00:20:00,967
I'll follow later.

388
00:20:02,267 --> 00:20:03,200
Go ahead.

389
00:20:03,333 --> 00:20:05,800
Mar, Abdul, take care
of grandmother, okay?

390
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:09,667
Don't let that family
oppress you.

391
00:20:09,800 --> 00:20:11,967
Yes, Grandmother. Just relax.

392
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:14,800
Take care of grandmother, okay?
Be careful.

393
00:20:14,933 --> 00:20:16,533
Okay. Take care, Bobby.

394
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:17,167
Okay.

395
00:20:20,133 --> 00:20:21,267
Thank you, Bobby.

396
00:20:32,433 --> 00:20:33,233
Bobby...

397
00:20:35,833 --> 00:20:38,967
I'm really, really sorry about
what happened with mom earlier.

398
00:20:41,667 --> 00:20:45,300
She was really hurt
because dad had cheated before.

399
00:20:45,433 --> 00:20:47,333
But what she did
was still wrong...

400
00:20:48,467 --> 00:20:49,800
so it's not your fault.

401
00:20:49,933 --> 00:20:52,100
I'm really sorry.
I'm really sorry, Bobby.

402
00:20:53,833 --> 00:20:54,900
That's okay, Faye.

403
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:01,067
Bobby, these are my friends,
Jhem and Jade.

404
00:21:01,200 --> 00:21:03,000
Hi!

405
00:21:03,133 --> 00:21:06,367
Ma'am Bobby, which station
are you assigned to?

406
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:07,567
Station 12.

407
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:13,267
Isn't that where Jako's older
brother, Monty, is being held?

408
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,967
Oh, yes.

409
00:21:15,100 --> 00:21:16,633
How's Monty doing there?

410
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:20,533
We're just waiting
for his hearing schedule.

411
00:21:20,667 --> 00:21:21,767
After that,

412
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:24,233
maybe he'll get transferred
to Calabari State Prison.

413
00:21:24,367 --> 00:21:25,633
What?

414
00:21:25,767 --> 00:21:27,667
He will be transferred?

415
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:30,667
I feel bad for Monty.

416
00:21:30,800 --> 00:21:32,800
What if he's innocent,

417
00:21:32,933 --> 00:21:35,633
and yet he's going to be put
with the really bad guys,

418
00:21:35,767 --> 00:21:38,533
the ones with serious cases?

419
00:21:38,667 --> 00:21:41,467
Hello, his case is serious!

420
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,067
Isn't he in jail

421
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:46,833
because he was supplying
pimple patch drugs to clubs?

422
00:21:52,633 --> 00:21:53,433
Bobby?

423
00:21:57,067 --> 00:21:57,933
Charlie?

424
00:22:08,467 --> 00:22:09,200
What are you doing here?

425
00:22:09,333 --> 00:22:10,533
Are you stalking me?

426
00:22:10,667 --> 00:22:13,467
Maybe you're the one
following me.

427
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:15,233
I've been coming here
for a long time.

428
00:22:15,400 --> 00:22:16,433
I'm a club member.

429
00:22:16,567 --> 00:22:17,933
Right, girls?

430
00:22:18,067 --> 00:22:19,600
How about you?

431
00:22:19,733 --> 00:22:21,000
She's with us.

432
00:22:21,133 --> 00:22:22,667
She's my half-sister.

433
00:22:25,367 --> 00:22:26,233
Wait...

434
00:22:26,367 --> 00:22:27,933
Aren't you the mayor's daughter?

435
00:22:29,367 --> 00:22:30,867
You mean...

436
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:32,067
she's your half-sister?

437
00:22:34,200 --> 00:22:37,833
Bobby, you didn't tell me...

438
00:22:37,967 --> 00:22:39,667
that you're the daughter
of the mayor's mistress.

439
00:22:42,467 --> 00:22:44,067
So that's why you got promoted.

440
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:46,733
Okay.

441
00:22:46,867 --> 00:22:48,233
Faye, excuse me...

442
00:22:52,400 --> 00:22:55,500
I got promoted because
I deserve it, Charlie.

443
00:22:56,533 --> 00:22:57,733
Sorry.

444
00:22:57,867 --> 00:22:59,167
Stop being so hot-headed.

445
00:22:59,300 --> 00:23:00,500
Okay, fine. You deserve
to be promoted.

446
00:23:00,633 --> 00:23:03,367
But of course, you know
that with connections,

447
00:23:03,500 --> 00:23:05,600
you can get promoted faster.

448
00:23:05,733 --> 00:23:07,933
You're really getting
on my nerves.

449
00:23:08,067 --> 00:23:10,167
Calm down, don't get angry.

450
00:23:11,333 --> 00:23:13,800
How about a swimming race?

451
00:23:13,933 --> 00:23:15,600
Like what we used to do?

452
00:23:15,733 --> 00:23:17,167
I don't have time for you.

453
00:23:20,033 --> 00:23:21,600
Excuse me, Faye.

454
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:22,400
Excuse me.

455
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:27,133
Bobby, this is your chance
to win...

456
00:23:27,267 --> 00:23:28,467
for a change.

457
00:23:28,600 --> 00:23:30,933
Why don't you represent
the children of the mistresses?

458
00:23:36,067 --> 00:23:38,700
You should be thankful I don't
have a swimsuit with me today.

459
00:23:38,833 --> 00:23:40,567
Otherwise, I'd race you.

460
00:23:44,300 --> 00:23:45,533
Bobby...

461
00:23:45,667 --> 00:23:47,400
do you need a swimsuit?

462
00:23:47,533 --> 00:23:49,133
We'll take care of it.
Right, girls?

463
00:23:49,267 --> 00:23:50,600
- Yes.
- Yes, Bobby.

464
00:23:50,733 --> 00:23:51,733
We got you.

465
00:23:59,833 --> 00:24:01,533
I know that girl.

466
00:24:02,967 --> 00:24:04,167
Who among them, Madam?

467
00:24:04,300 --> 00:24:05,600
They are all girls.

468
00:24:07,833 --> 00:24:10,100
My new ally.

469
00:24:19,533 --> 00:24:23,667
Why are women ghosting men?

470
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,467
Are you talking about
Doc Cecilia, Sir?

471
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:26,633
She has a boyfriend.

472
00:24:26,767 --> 00:24:27,967
I haven't answered her yet.

473
00:24:28,100 --> 00:24:30,433
It's Vice Mayor Glen Guerrero.

474
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:33,200
He said if you escape
from here,

475
00:24:33,333 --> 00:24:35,100
you'll need to work for him.

476
00:24:35,233 --> 00:24:36,300
No problem.

477
00:24:36,433 --> 00:24:38,633
I'm just going to cross
someone off my list.

478
00:24:38,767 --> 00:24:39,600
It's Conde.

479
00:24:39,733 --> 00:24:41,967
We can't just rush in.

480
00:24:42,100 --> 00:24:43,300
What are we going to do?

481
00:24:43,433 --> 00:24:44,167
Let's help each other.

482
00:24:44,300 --> 00:24:48,733
Three, two, one, go!

483
00:24:48,867 --> 00:24:50,633
Go, Bobby!

484
00:24:50,767 --> 00:24:52,300
Hurry up!

485
00:24:52,433 --> 00:24:56,033
Enriquez is planning to transfer
to Calabari Prison.

486
00:24:56,167 --> 00:24:57,900
Enriquez wants
to transfer there?

487
00:24:58,033 --> 00:24:59,333
Is she serious about it?
